# REVERSE PROXY CONFIGURATION (Express 'trust proxy')
# This setting is required when running behind a reverse proxy (Traefik, Nginx, Cloudflare, etc.)
# to correctly identify client IP addresses for rate limiting.
#
# Possible values:
# - '1' (Number): Trust the first hop. Recommended for a single proxy like Traefik or Nginx.
# - '2' (Number): Trust the 2nd hop. Use if you have a CDN (like Cloudflare) + a local proxy.
# - 'true' (Boolean): Trust all 'X-Forwarded-*' headers. Easy for local/trusted networks but
#                    allows IP spoofing if the proxy isn't sanitizing headers.
# - 'false' (Boolean): Do not trust any proxy. (Express default)
# - 'loopback' (String): Trust loopback addresses (127.0.0.1/8, ::1/128).
# - '10.0.0.1, 192.168.1.1' (IP list): Trust a specific list of proxy IP addresses.
# - '10.0.0.0/8' (Subnet): Trust an entire CIDR range.
TRUST_PROXY=1